OL,3,CWhat is family voting and was it an
OL,4,Cissue in the Gorton and Denton by-
OL,5,Celection?
OL,7,FAs is normal after an election, the
OL,8,Fwinning side and the losing side often
OL,9,Fhave different answers to the
OL,10,Fquestion, but this time, different
OL,11,Felection monitors have differing views.
OL,13,FDemocracy Volunteers first raised the
OL,14,Fissue while votes were being counted.
OL,15,FTheir director, John Ault said: "Based
OL,16,Fon our assessment of today's
OL,17,Fobservations, we have seen the highest
OL,18,Flevels of family voting at any
OL,19,Felection in our 10-year history of
OL,20,Fobserving elections in the UK.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1772216417
OL,3,CWhat is family voting and was it an
OL,4,Cissue in the Gorton and Denton by-
OL,5,Celection?
OL,7,F"We rarely issue a report on the night
OL,8,Fof an election, but the data we have
OL,9,Fcollected today on family voting, when
OL,10,Fcompared to other recent by-elections,
OL,11,Fis extremely high.
OL,13,F"In the other recent Westminster
OL,14,Fparliamentary by-election in Runcorn
OL,15,Fand Helsby we saw family voting in 12%
OL,16,Fof polling stations, affecting 1% of
OL,17,Fvoters. In Gorton and Denton, we
OL,18,Fobserved family voting in 68% of
OL,19,Fpolling stations, affecting 12% of
OL,20,Fthose voters observed."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
